speech-writer, and among the dithyrambic poets, Licymnius.

The Same: Now a term should be applied only in speaking of a class and a real distinction: other- wise it is empty and mere nonsense, like the term used by Licymnius in his Art, where he speaks of ‘ speeding-on ’ and ‘ aberration ' and ‘ raniifications.'

Scholiast on the passage: (a) Licymnius, who was one of the dithyramb-writers, was an accurate writer of prose31 (b) Licymnius was an orator; it was to repetition that he gave the name of ‘ speeding-on.’
